metadata.doc:
jumpToNextFileStartingWith jumps to the next file/directory starting with the given letter
This enables quick navigation via Shift+Letter (e.g., Shift+R to jump to files starting with 'R')
loadFileContent loads the content of a file
navigateToSelectedFile navigates to the currently selected file
navigateUp navigates to the parent directory
screenToDocCoords transforms screen coordinates to document coordinates
startMouseSelection initializes mouse-based text selection with timeout recovery
transitionTo cleanly transitions between UI modes
updateDimensions recalculates layout dimensions based on window size
ClearSelection clears the current selection

CopySelection copies text to system clipboard
If a selection is active, copy the selected text
Otherwise, copy the entire content
ExtendSelection extends selection to a new position
GetSelection returns the currently selected text from content
GetSelectionBounds returns the selection start and end as (startLine, startCol, endLine, endCol)
HasSelection returns whether text is currently selected
StartSelection marks the beginning of a selection
GetColor returns a color by name from the current palette
GetStyle returns a styled text element
PrintThemeInfo prints information about the current theme
SetTheme changes the current theme
applyTheme applies the current theme
detectBackgroundColor attempts to detect the terminal background color
detectTheme detects the terminal background color and returns appropriate palette
getDetectedTheme returns the theme that was detected
loadConfig loads the color configuration from disk
saveConfig saves the color configuration to disk
Clear resets all panel data
CycleMode switches to the next display mode
GetModeName returns the current mode name
GetTOC returns the TOC component
Render renders the context panel based on current mode
SetMode sets a specific mode
UpdateContent analyzes content and updates all modes
renderDocumentStats renders document statistics
renderFileInfo renders file metadata
renderQuickActions renders quick actions menu
renderTOC renders the table of contents
updateDocumentStats analyzes markdown structure
updateFileInfo calculates file metadata
GetBackground returns the background color.
GetForeground returns the foreground color.
BuildFileIndex builds a complete index of all files (one-time, then cached)
GetResultCount returns number of results
GetResults returns current search results
GetSelectedIndex returns current selection index
GetSelectedResult returns the currently selected result
Search performs a fuzzy search on the file index
SelectNext moves to next result
SelectPrevious moves to previous result
View renders the search results as a string
Changes returns a channel that receives change notifications
Close stops the file watcher and releases resources
SetDebounce sets the debounce duration
SetEventFilter sets which event types to filter out
SetRecursive enables/disables recursive directory watching
Unwatch removes a path from the watch list
Watch adds a path to the watch list
eventLoop processes fsnotify events

followSymlinksWithLoopDetection resolves symlinks while detecting circular references.
Returns error if symlink loop detected or max depth (40) exceeded.
Uses inode tracking to detect cycles efficiently.
handleEvent processes a single fsnotify event

shouldFilterEvent checks if an event should be filtered based on event type.
Uses RLock for efficient concurrent reads.
Cursor returns the current cursor position.
Filter returns the current filter query.
FilteredResults returns the current filtered item list.
HandleKey processes navigation keys with wrapping support.
JumpToLetter moves cursor to the first item starting with the given letter.
Mode returns the current interaction mode.
SelectedItem returns the currently selected item.
SetCursor sets the cursor position if within valid bounds.
SetFilter applies a filter query and updates filtered results.
SetMode sets the current interaction mode.
AutoDetectSize would detect terminal size (placeholder).

DetectedTheme returns the current theme setting.
Thread-safe: uses read lock.
GetElementStyle returns styling for a specific markdown element.

NewViewport creates a viewport for scrollable content.
Thread-safe: uses read lock to access width.

Render converts markdown to terminal-formatted output.
Lazy-initializes renderer on first call. Returns formatted string or error.
Thread-safe: uses read lock to safely access width during rendering.
RenderSearchResult formats a search result for display.

SetTheme manually overrides the theme.
Thread-safe: uses write lock to update theme.

SetWidth updates the rendering width.
Thread-safe: uses write lock to update width.

Width returns the current rendering width.
Thread-safe: uses read lock.
WrapEnabled returns whether word wrapping is enabled.

initializeRenderer creates the glamour renderer with current settings.
Thread-safe: acquires read lock before accessing width.
GetMode returns the current interaction mode.

HandleKey processes a key event based on the current mode.
Returns nil to signal exit, otherwise returns the updated model.
SetMode updates the current interaction mode.
SelectLine selects the current line
SelectWord selects from current position to end of word

QuickSearchFiles performs a simple contains-based search
Useful for immediate feedback while building full index

Execute runs ripgrep with the given query and returns results via channel.
Results are streamed asynchronously. The channel is closed when search completes or context is canceled.
Returns error if query validation fails or ripgrep is not installed.

ExecuteWithLimit runs ripgrep with a maximum result count.
Automatically stops consuming results after maxResults are reached.
SetBufferSize configures the buffer size for streaming
SetCaseSensitive configures case sensitivity
SetContextLines configures before/after context lines
SetFileTypes sets file type filters

checkRipgrepAvailable verifies ripgrep is installed and available in PATH.
Result is cached to avoid repeated checks. Returns helpful error message if missing.
Thread-safe using sync.Once.
validateQuery checks query for potential shell injection attacks.
Search executes a search query and returns parsed matches
SetMaxConcurrent sets the maximum concurrent searches
JumpToLevel shows entries of a specific level or higher (collapsing deeper levels)
GetEntryCount returns the number of TOC entries
GetHierarchy returns a tree-like structure of the TOC
GetSelectedEntry returns the currently selected TOC entry
GetSelectedIndex returns the current selection index
GetSelectedLineNum returns the line number of the selected entry
HasEntries returns whether the TOC has any entries
ParseMarkdown extracts headers from markdown content
SearchTOC finds entries matching a search term
SelectByIndex selects a specific entry by index

SelectByLineNum selects the entry closest to a given line number
Useful for syncing viewer scroll with TOC
SelectFirst jumps to the first TOC entry
SelectLast jumps to the last TOC entry
SelectNext moves to the next TOC entry
SelectPrevious moves to the previous TOC entry
View renders the table of contents
Height returns the viewport height.
NeedsReflow indicates if content needs to be reflowed.
SetContent updates the viewport content.
SetYOffset updates the vertical scroll offset.
Width returns the viewport width.
YOffset returns the current vertical scroll offset.
AppModel represents the complete application state
Init initializes the model
Update handles messages and updates the model
View renders the UI
handleMouseEvent processes mouse events for text selection and scrolling
highlightSelection applies visual highlighting to selected text
renderFinderModal renders the fuzzy finder modal overlay using flat state (Blocker 2 Fix)
renderLoadingModal renders a loading indicator
renderSearchModal renders the ripgrep search UI (Phase 3 Week 2)
ClipboardManager handles copy/paste operations
ColorManager manages the application's color theme
ColorPalette defines all colors used in the application
ContextPanel manages the right panel display with multiple modes
ContextPanelMode represents different display modes for the right panel
CopyMode represents different copy modes
DefaultKeyBindings returns the default vim-style keybindings
DocumentStats holds statistics about markdown content
ElementStyle provides styling for markdown elements.
ExampleCustomConfig returns an example custom configuration
File Watcher Messages (Phase 3 Week 3)
FileInfo holds metadata about the current file
FileItem represents a file or directory in the file tree
Implement list.Item interface for FileItem
FileSearcher performs fast file search

FileWatcher monitors file system changes with debouncing and filtering.
All methods are safe for concurrent use from multiple goroutines.

FileWatcherImpl implements FileWatcher using fsnotify.
Thread-safe implementation with debouncing and event filtering.
Fuzzy Finder Messages
FuzzyFinder interface (to be implemented)

FuzzyFinderImpl provides fuzzy finding and filtering for a list of items.
Supports navigation with wrapping, case-insensitive filtering, and jump-to-letter.
Thread-safe for concurrent reads (cursor, filter state).
GlamourRenderer interface (to be implemented)

GlamourRendererImpl handles markdown rendering with theme detection.
Lazy-initializes renderer on first use for efficiency.
Thread-safe implementation using RWMutex for concurrent access.
KeyBinding represents a single key action
KeyBindings represents the complete keybinding configuration
FindAction returns the action for a given key in a view context
KeybindingHandler manages keyboard input routing and mode-aware key dispatch.
KeyboardSelection handles keyboard-based text selection
LoadKeyBindings loads keybindings from config file, or returns defaults
Async File Loading (Blocker 1 Fix)
MockFileSystemProvider provides filesystem abstraction for testing
MockFilesystemWatcher provides file watching abstraction with fsnotify
MockRipgrepExecutor provides ripgrep command execution abstraction
Mouse Drag Timeout (Blocker 3 Fix)
NewAppModel creates a new application model
NewClipboardManager creates a new clipboard manager
NewColorManager creates a new color manager with automatic theme detection
NewContextPanel creates a new context panel
NewElementStyle creates a style for a markdown element.
NewFileSearcher creates a new file searcher

NewFileWatcher creates a new FileWatcher instance.
Returns nil if fsnotify initialization fails.
Default configuration: 200ms debounce, chmod events filtered, recursive watching enabled.
NewFuzzyFinder creates a new fuzzy finder instance
NewFuzzyFinderImpl creates a new fuzzy finder with the given items.
NewGlamourRenderer creates a new Glamour renderer instance

NewGlamourRendererImpl creates a new glamour renderer with auto-detected theme.
Default width: 80 columns. Renderer is lazy-initialized on first Render() call.
NewKeybindingHandler creates a new keybinding handler in normal mode.
NewKeyboardSelection creates a keyboard selection handler
NewQuickSearch creates a quick search for immediate results

NewRipgrepExecutor creates a new ripgrep executor instance.
Default configuration: 4 concurrent searches, 32KB buffer, case-insensitive.
NewRipgrepManager creates a new ripgrep manager with concurrency limits
NewTableOfContents creates a new TOC
ParseRipgrepMatch parses a ripgrep message into a match
QuickSearch is a simpler, faster search using string containment

RipgrepExecutorImpl executes ripgrep searches with concurrency control.
Thread-safe implementation using semaphore for limiting concurrent searches.
RipgrepManager interface for concurrent search management
RipgrepManagerImpl implements RipgrepManager
RipgrepMatch represents a parsed match result
RipgrepMessage represents a JSON message from ripgrep
RipgrepResult represents a single search result from ripgrep
SearchResult represents a single search result
Ripgrep Search Messages (Phase 3 Week 2)
SelectionMode represents text selection state in viewer
SelectionState represents text selection in the viewer
Style interface (to be implemented)
TOCEntry represents a heading in the table of contents
TableOfContents represents the complete TOC structure
ThemeConfig represents the saved theme configuration
ThemeMode represents the color theme
UIMode represents the current UI interaction mode (State Machine)
ViewMode represents the current view/pane focus
Viewport interface (to be implemented)
ViewportImpl manages scrollable content display.
Helper function
createDefaultConfig creates the default config file

detectTheme determines light/dark theme from COLORFGBG environment variable.
Format: "foreground;background" where background > 7 indicates light theme.
Defaults to dark theme if detection fails.
dragTimeoutCmd creates a timeout command for mouse drag recovery (Blocker 3 Fix)
extractSelection extracts text from lines based on selection state
filterItems performs case-insensitive substring filtering
findMarkdownFiles recursively finds all markdown files in a directory
formatBytes formats bytes into human-readable format

fuzzyMatch performs fuzzy matching and returns a score
Higher score = better match
GetConfigDir returns the config directory path
getHelpOverlay returns a styled help overlay for in-app display with theme support
highlightMatch creates a highlighted display string
loadDirectory loads files from a directory
loadMarkdownFilesCmd asynchronously loads markdown files (Blocker 1 Fix)
navigateCursor wraps cursor navigation with boundary checking
printHelp displays the CLI help information
printKeyboardShortcuts displays keyboard shortcuts reference
printVersion displays version information
shouldIgnoreDir returns true if directory should be skipped
sortByScore sorts results by fuzzy match score (highest first)
splitLines splits content into lines
GetStyle returns the current style
Render renders markdown content
SetStyle changes the rendering style
UpdateWidth updates the renderer width
MarkdownRenderer handles markdown rendering
MarkdownStyle represents available rendering styles
NewMarkdownRenderer creates a new markdown renderer with auto-detected theme
NewMarkdownRendererWithStyle creates a renderer with a specific style
